history.content:
I'm pretty sure as long as you get into lecture (which #15 on the waitlist is very probable) you will be fine for the class.

Discussions will probably be open attendance so you can attend any of the ones that they have time slots open for. However, try to go to the ones that are less crowded if you can and it's better to get to know your GSI.

@730 for reference

When I signed up for the waitlist on CS70 (i'm a declared major switching into EECS), I was put as ~60 on the lecture waitlist and I was the first person on the waitlist for my discussion. 

Now when there is open spots in that discussion, other people on the waitlist are still getting into the discussion before me even though it is currently adjustment period - because the website says that EECS/CoE undeclared/CS will be prioritized "Until the end of undergraduate Phase II appointments" but its currently adjustment period. 

Is this supposed to be happening? 

If i'm currently #15 on the waitlist for the lecture and I assume i'm still first on the waitlist for that discussion, can i still get in or will other people still be prioritized in the discussions?
